    "narrative": "The clear anchor for today\u2019s lineup is **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite 81.53 score against Civale. With a favorable park factor and strong SP skill leverage, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is our primary source of run production. Following him, **Jonathan Aranda** (65.18), **Geraldo Perdomo** (64.30), and **Taylor Ward** (64.19) represent our core of high-efficiency plays. **Geraldo Perdomo** is particularly intriguing; despite a moderate matchup against Boyd, the wind blowing out adds significant weight to his base, while **Taylor Ward** benefits from a premium leadoff spot and a platoon advantage that keeps him in strong starting territory despite facing Fried.\n\nThe decision to bench **Luis Arraez** (43.84) was the most difficult call of the morning. While **Luis Arraez** offers a stable floor for AVG, the optimizer prioritized the higher upside in the SB and HR categories found in our fringe starters like **Daulton Varsho** and **Masyn Winn**. Even though **Masyn Winn** faces a tough arm in Wrobleski, his stolen base potential\u2014fueled by the SP's slow delivery\u2014keeps his score ahead of the more stationary bats on our bench. We are tracking a few risks today: **Wenceel Perez** and **Gleyber Torres** are currently based on pending lineups; should their confirmed batting orders slide down, their efficiency scores will crater. Furthermore, we are proceeding with caution on **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Daulton Varsho** as they face significant pitcher-skill headwinds, requiring us to monitor these games closely to preserve our weekly cap usage if the early innings suggest a suppressed scoring environment.",
